description:
Each year when The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide arrives with new prices, new feature articles, new additions to the Overstreet Hall of Fame, and more, it's an annual event, and this year will be no different. The book referred to as "The Bible of collectors and dealers" returns with its 46th edition, including market reports from top retailers and experienced fans. Harley Quinn, Power Girl, Supergirl, and Before Watchmen: Silk Spectre artist Amanda Conner provides the cover. The comic book medium is making history, and history starts right here.

description: Camilla d'Errico's first-ever adult coloring book featuring black-and-white renderings of her surreal, beautiful, and haunting manga-inspired images.Painter and manga superstar Camilla d'Errico is back again, this time with an adult coloring book featuring her one-of-a-kind, manga-influenced artwork that fans and art collectors around the world have come to love and desire. Pop Manga Coloring Book is a special coloring experience and one of the few to feature artwork of an artist at the top of her field.
name: SC

description: Collecting the first five issue of the hit series REPLICA, from Paul Jenkins and Andy Clarke. Meet Trevor Churchill, an Earth-born peacekeeping agent on the intergalactic hub known as The Transfer. When Trevor's already near impossible assignment becomes a bit too much for the errant detective, he turns to the only logical approach, Replication. More of a good thing can't hurt, right? A single clone could be helpful; unfortunately the replication process doesn't go as planned!
name: Volume 1

description: Just as the curtain is about to fall on the monstrous crimes of The Wednesday Club, the tables are turned again and Ray Pilgrim is forced to choose between two great evils.
name: Line of Sight

description:
First, after teaming up with Flare to tackle some dinosaurs and purple gorillas, it's Billi Jayne's first day on her new job at Hunter Electronics. But it may be that she doesn't quite understand exactly what it is her "uncle" Donald Hunter (aka the Huntsman) actually expects her to be doing. "Working Girl" is by Dennis Mallonee and Giancarlo Caracuzzo.

Then, Billi Jayne visits New York to take on the threat of BIG BROTHER in an all-new adventure plotted, drawn, and colored by James Webb, with a teensy bit of scripting help from the G-Girl's creator, Dennis Mallonee.
name: Working Girl; First Little Brother, Now Big Brother

description: Bestselling author Rysa Walker (Timebound) takes readers on a time-hopping adventure in this stand-alone series set in her Chronos Files world. Nineteen-year-old Clio Dunne has lived a life of secrecy. Her world-saving, time-travelling parents have kept a low profile in a boring, small town, but Clio yearns for her own adventure. In the fall of 1931, Clio packs her bags and heads to the big, modern city of Chicago. While following her dreams of becoming a famous illustrator, Clio's own nascent skills as a time traveler are put to the test. A nasty acquaintance from her parents' past stumbles upon Clio in an unexpected place-the trial of Al Capone! Now Clio must jump through time to keep the past, present, and future safe.

Wandering Star is a beautiful story, written years before its time. This much-praised space drama follows the far-flung adventures of Cassandra, daughter of the President of the United Nations and the first terran accepted into the Galactic Academy. Cassandra discovers to her woe that Earth isn't the most popular of planets and joins the outcasts working on the Wandering Star, the Alliance's prototypical spaceship. When the Bono Kiro, the Alliance's longtime enemy, makes a sudden reappearance, Cassandra and her misfit crew just might turn out to be the galaxy's last hope. Sure to delight the legions of fans of the series, this beautiful hardcover edition collects all 21 of the original comics for the first time.
name: HC

description: Drew Jackson's father didn't want Drew to have just any DC summer internship, he wanted Drew to intern for a Cabinet position! And Drew got one, for the United States Witchfinder General, a dusty basement office that's everyone forgot about. 'Cause really, why would the U.S.of A. need to worry anymore about witches?
name: TPB

description: After finding their hosts murdered, traveling dolls embark upon a nightmarish road trip in this inspired piece of gothic noir. Disguised as a children's book, this dark and disturbing work is filled with hauntingly lifelike pen-and-ink illustrations. New Foreword by Shaun Tan (The Lost Thing).
name: GN

description: Check out the what’s next from DC with this digital edition of the DC COMICS AUGUST 2016 PREVIEWS CATALOG! Find out about the newest series from DC’s YOUNG ANIMAL—CAVE CARSON HAS A MAGNETIC EYE and SHADE, THE CHANGING GIRL—see what’s in store for DC UNIVERSE: REBIRTH, and get the scoop on brand new mini-series starring Hawkman and Adam Strange, Deadman, Midnighter and Apollo, and, for the first time, He-Man and the Thundercats! Also included are the rest of the October on-sale comics, plus trade paperbacks and hardcovers, new items from DC Collectibles and more!

Get a first look at all of the epic DC Comics titles coming out in August 2016 from the June Previews Catalogue. Check out newly launching REBIRTH series SUPERGIRL, SUICIDE SQUAD, ALL-STAR BATMAN by Scott Snyder with art by John Romita Jr. and more! Also included are the rest of the August on-sale comics, plus trade paperbacks and hardcovers, new items from DC Collectibles and more!

Check out all the DC comics coming out in September 2016 with the July Previews Catalogue. Get first looks at the new DC'S YOUNG ANIMAL series DOOM PATROL, brand new REBIRTH series CYBORG and TRINITY! Also included are the rest of the September on-sale comics, plus trade paperbacks and hardcovers, new items from DC Collectibles and more!
